        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/17766",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Why should an Array Adapter accept Strings ?\n\nAs per definition of the class name the usage is for \"Arrays\"...\nYou can simply extend any existing adapter or write your own.\n\nBut I don't think that a \"string\" Adapter is usefull, because you could simply do\n\n{code}\n$t->addTranslation(array($key => $value));\n{code}",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-12-03T13:07:18.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-12-03T13:07:18.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/17768",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=laurent+melmoux",
                        "name": "laurent melmoux",
                        "displayName": "Laurent Melmoux",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Well, if you can do both its even better don't you think? :)\nThere are a lot of classes in the frameworks were the argument is an object or a string, and in the later it will use a factory to get the object. So it could be done with array too.\n\nBut best, if you can provide a string the array adapter will work with the automatic source detection. My $0.2",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=laurent+melmoux",
                        "name": "laurent melmoux",
                        "displayName": "Laurent Melmoux",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-12-03T13:56:56.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-12-03T13:56:56.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/17808",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "It's not just that 3 lines.\nWe have also to handle output and failures from the file.\n\nAnyway, it has been integrated with SVN-7050.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-12-06T07:49:41.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-12-06T07:49:41.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/17809",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=laurent+melmoux",
                        "name": "laurent melmoux",
                        "displayName": "Laurent Melmoux",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Thanks Thomas ! :)\n\n{quote}\nIt's not just that 3 lines\nWe have also to handle output and failures from the file.\n{quote}\n\nThat's right.\n\nI think there is a more appropriated test \n{code}\nif(is_string($data)) \n{code}\n\nInstead of the one I first suggested \n{code}\nif(!is_array($data))\n{code}",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=laurent+melmoux",
                        "name": "laurent melmoux",
                        "displayName": "Laurent Melmoux",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-12-06T08:09:49.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-12-06T08:09:49.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
